# S05-T02: Agent-Role Taxonomy (organization layer)

## Objective
Put the agnostic agent-role taxonomy where every app inherits it (invariant §6).

## Execution
- In `organization/app/app.config.ts`, add an `agents` block:
  - `roles`: PLANNER, PM, ARCHITECT, QA, TEST_AUTHOR, DEVOPS, ROOT, OPTIMIZER.
  - Per role: `label`, `icon` (lucide), `color` (Nuxt UI token), `blurb`.
  - `defaultLeadByLayer`: { chat: ROOT, epic: PM, board: PLANNER, task: <derived> }.
- Add a typed accessor in `apps/work-control` (composable `useAgentRoles()`) that reads
  `useAppConfig().agents` — do NOT hardcode the list in the app.
- Keep ONLY the agnostic taxonomy in organization; per-app behavior stays in T11 docs.

## Out
`organization/app/app.config.ts` (agents block) + `apps/work-control/.../useAgentRoles.ts`

## Done when
- `useAppConfig().agents.roles` resolves in work-control; lint passes.
